../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:19:This is the softest part of the original chain. The attack is right that the candidate family sits close to known alignment literature and that "bounded observable" is far too weak a filter. The refinement needs an explicit quantitative gate: each admitted candidate must point to a concrete inequality or sign/coercivity statement on the full stretching term, not just geometric plausibility.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:34:The novelty check is indeed too late in the original version. In a literature-heavy area like stretching, alignment, and pressure-Hessian geometry, overlap must be audited before candidate selection hardens. The attack is also right that theorem-shaped propositions can disguise circularity unless the missing theorem is proved to be narrower than full regularity.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:75:Most likely presentable result: a sharp obstruction memo showing that tensor-level alignment or misalignment data remains informative but non-coercive once representation dependence, eigenvalue degeneracy, and full pressure-Hessian debt are charged honestly.
