../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:205:The critique is right that exact Beltrami flows are too nongeneric to serve as positive confirmation of a generic NS mechanism, and the mission context already records that the cancellation is not robust under very small perturbation. It is also correct that an undefined notion of "small perturbation away from Beltrami alignment" is too loose.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:244:- If the branch becomes primarily about alignment geometry, it has drifted into Chain 03 territory.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:275:- and treat Beltrami/alignment behavior only as a fragility screen and branch-handoff condition.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:320:   The best geometry-first candidate. It targets NS-specific vortex structure rather than norms or compactness machinery, and its negative outcomes remain useful because they cleanly separate local geometric depletion from global alignment fantasy.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:323:   Strong reserve candidate, but weaker portfolio fit than Chain 03. It is promising as a bridge chain, yet it overlaps part of Chain 03's `S omega`/alignment axis and part of Chain 01's pressure-structure axis, so it adds less marginal diversity to the selected set.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:340:The attack is largely correct. The original chain points at a real NS-specific direction, but it understates the central obstruction: local Beltrami alignment, vorticity-direction coherence, and vortex-tube persistence are not the same mechanism, and the missing bridge between them is the whole problem, not a downstream detail. The chain should be kept, but only in a stricter, obstruction-first form.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:348:The original chain does treat local Beltrami alignment, `xi`-regularity, and tube persistence as if they naturally reinforce one another. Heuristically they are related, but no quantitative implication is supplied. Any refined plan has to separate them and ask which, if any, can actually feed a known regularity mechanism.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:360:This is the strongest critique. The dangerous term is vortex stretching, `S omega`, not the Lamb vector `u x omega`. Small local Beltrami deficit does not by itself control `S omega` or `S omega . omega`, and local tube-core alignment does not remove exterior contributions to strain. A plan that cannot address the full stretching term should terminate as a fragility result.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:469:- Expected output: a formula sheet containing `I_p^far`, the role of `C_far`, the surviving modes, and a one-page Tao-gate note.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:565:- Action: if one candidate appears to improve the estimate, test whether the gain is genuinely algebraic and generic or merely a near-Beltrami / alignment effect.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:568:  - the gain persists outside special alignment classes and remains a live algebraic lead, or
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-final-decider.log:570:- Kill condition: if the candidate only survives in exact or near-exact Beltrami-style alignment, record "geometry branch only" and close this chain as an algebraic dead end.
