../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-004-attacker-03.log:461:+The fair verdict is that this chain should be run mainly as a negative-discovery program. If it succeeds, the success standard has to be very high: not a prettier tensor identity, not a reduced eigenframe toy model, and not another alignment-flavored criterion, but a mechanism that survives full nonlocal coupling and clearly breaks beyond what Tao-style averaging preserves. Anything short of that is obstruction mapping, not a live route.
