+
+Equivalent-packaging screening should stop an endpoint-first branch before
+tensor-package freeze whenever no packaging-independent gain on the same live
+coefficient is on disk.
+
+Reusable lesson:
+
+- exact identities, eigenframe language, restricted-Euler defects, and local /
+  harmonic decompositions should be treated as equivalent packagings unless one
+  of them returns to the same theorem-level bad term with a smaller effective
+  coefficient;
+- Tao sensitivity and NS-specific wording do not rescue a family that stays
+  non-coercive on the reconstructed full pairing;
+- and if every packaging collapses into representation convenience, local
+  geometry, reduced-model language, or criterion restatement, the branch should
+  stop at the repackaging gate rather than opening Step 3 rhetorically.
+
+For this step, no packaging of the remaining pressure-Hessian family produced a
+smaller coefficient on the full `I_p^far` pairing, so the honest verdict is
+branch stop before tensor-package freeze.
